criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age over than or equal to 60 years;

          2. Bilateral or unilateral OA of the knee diagnosed according to clinical and
             radiological criteria of the American College of Rheumatology (ACR)(Altman et al.,
             1986);

          3. Independent mobility;

          4. and reading and writing knowledge.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Not be involved in another intervention program (exercise, education or physical
             therapy;

          2. Do not use supplements (chondroitin sulfate and / or glucosamine) for at least three
             months;

          3. Have other pathology (cardiovascular, respiratory, musculoskeletal, cancer) that
             prevents physical exercise;

          4. Mental / psychological state hindering understanding of the program;

          5. Having undergone surgery for knee replacement or going perform this surgery in the
             next eight months;

          6. Being allergic to shellfish;

          7. Have made injections of corticosteroids or hyaluronic acid in the last 6 months
